  <p>
    The Independent School of Jakarta was represented at the British Embassy in Jakarta for a policy discussion on character building in the digital era. The event brought together educators, policymakers, and community leaders to explore how schools and families can nurture positive values and resilience in a technology-driven world.
  </p>

  <img src="/images/news/character-building-embassy.jpg" alt="ISJ at the British Embassy Jakarta" class="img-wide" loading="lazy" />

  <p>
    Eileen Fisher, Head of ISJ, contributed to the discussion by emphasising the vital role that parents and the wider community play in supporting character development and promoting cyber safety among young people.
  </p>

  <p>
    ISJ's participation reflects the school's commitment to developing responsible, empathetic, and digitally aware global citizens, both inside and outside the classroom.
  </p>

